# 📊 DQ'INSIGHT: Data Quality Assessment Tool

DQ'INSIGHT is a user-friendly Streamlit application designed to assess and improve the quality of your data. Whether you're uploading a CSV or exploring a PDF, this tool offers interactive summaries, visualisations, and machine learning functionality to support your data journey.


# 🚀 Features
🔹 Project Structure
app.py: Main Streamlit app.
data/: Sample datasets.
utils/: Utility functions for loading, checking, and visualising data.
assets/: Static files (e.g., images, styles).


# 📂 Upload and Summarise PDF Files
Extract and view text from uploaded PDF documents.
Automatically generate text summaries.
Example: Try it with Making-Laws.pdf.

# 📊 Data Quality (DQ) Checks on CSV Files
Assess your dataset for:
Missing Data: Highlights null or missing values.
Outliers: Detects extreme values.
Inconsistencies: Flags mismatched patterns (e.g., date formats).
Duplications: Identifies duplicate rows.
Invalid Values: Detects out-of-range or erroneous values.
Data Type Errors: Highlights column-type mismatches.

# 📈 Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
Upload CSV files (up to 200MB).
Preview data and view default visualisations.
Customise charts by selecting X and Y axes.
Save your customised visualisations.
Example: Use the daily-bike-share.csv file provided.

# 🤖 Machine Learning Functionality
Step-by-step guide to applying machine learning to your dataset.
Includes deployment suggestions and best practices.

# 📋 Results & Recommendations
Review your results after running checks or models.
Get actionable recommendations for data improvement or model deployment.
💡 Use the sidebar to navigate through all features.

# 🛠️ How to Run the App
1. Clone the repository:
git clone https://github.com/annorv/dqinsight.git
cd dqinsight

2. Create and activate a virtual environment:
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate   # On Windows: venv\Scripts\activate

3. Install the dependencies:
pip install -r requirements.txt

4. Run the app:
streamlit run app.py